    "id": "cdx_ig_46_cdso_vol",
    "description": "CDX.NA.IG.46 CDS index option (CDSO) volatility surface calibrated from a 3×3 (expiry × strike) grid of lognormal spread-vol quotes, chained on a USD-OIS discount curve and CDX-NA-IG-46 hazard curve that are bootstrapped in the same plan. Step 1 produces the USD-OIS discount curve from deposit and IRS quotes; step 2 calibrates the CDX-NA-IG-46 index hazard curve from realistic par-spread CDS quotes (50/75/100/110/120 bp); step 3 fits the CDSO vol surface. The envelope is fully self-bootstrapping from quotes — no hand-entered curves in initial_market. The vol_surface step uses OptionVol quotes where underlying='CDX-NA-IG-46' and strikes are CDS spread levels in decimal (e.g., 0.0075 = 75bp). The SABR model is calibrated per-expiry with β=1.0 (lognormal) and spot_override = 0.01 (~100bp), matching the 5y par spread implied by the chained hazard curve (realistic CDX-IG-46 levels). The produced VolSurface is keyed as 'CDX-NA-IG-46-CDSO-VOL' and is retrievable via MarketContext::get_surface(). Note: settings.fail_on_bad_fit is set to false because the input grid is flat in the strike dimension; SABR (β=1) cannot pin a near-flat smile to engine tolerance (1e-12) when ν is bounded away from zero. The produced surface is queryable but does not pin to the input quotes at solver tolerance — replace with a non-flat smile (e.g., +/- 50bps of vol on the 0.0075 / 0.0125 bp wings) to exercise SABR with strict fit.",
